The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 February is 39,874 (4,615.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 February, there were 738 new confirmed cases (85.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 February, there were 935 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 21% (197 fewer cases).
